The paper presents a framework for solving the Vehicle Routing Problem (VRP) using deep reinforcement learning, which involves training a single model to find near-optimal solutions for problem instances. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves optimization and decision-making, which are key components of Robotics (cs.RO) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper's focus on real-time solutions and policy optimization suggests that it may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
